<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0e64c7fc-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9548"><num value="9548">§ 9548.</num><heading> State defined</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this part, the term “State” means each of the 50 States, the District of Columbia, and the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0e64c7fd-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/279/tI/s158">Pub. L. 107–279, title I, § 158</ref>, <date date="2002-11-05">Nov. 5, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1962">116 Stat. 1962</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
